   "start": 67.28,
   "end": 67.5
  },
  {
   "w": "stacktags",
   "start": 67.5,
   "end": 68.08
  },
  {
   "w": ".io",
   "start": 68.08,
   "end": 68.66
  }
 ],
 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 2.52,
   "text": "There's one thing you must never do with chopsticks in China."
  },
  {
   "start": 3.0,
   "end": 4.66,
   "text": "Stand them straight up in your bowl of rice."
  },
  {
   "start": 5.06,
   "end": 6.62,
   "text": "Do it and you've just set a place."
  },
  {
   "start": 7.08,
   "end": 7.66,
   "text": "For the dead."
  },
  {
   "start": 8.14,
   "end": 9.66,
   "text": "Here's why this one looks so wrong."
  },
  {
   "start": 10.1,
   "end": 14.38,
   "text": "It's one of the deepest dining taboos in Chinese culture, and the reason is what it resembles."
  },
  {
   "start": 14.92,
   "end": 20.12,
   "text": "At funerals and ancestor rituals, a bowl of rice with incense or chopsticks standing"
  },
  {
   "start": 20.12,
   "end": 21.84,
   "text": "straight up is offered to the deceased."
  },
  {
   "start": 22.3,
   "end": 23.28,
   "text": "It's a gift for the dead."
  },
  {
   "start": 23.62,
   "end": 27.72,
   "text": "So at a normal dinner, chopsticks jammed upright look exactly like a death offering."
  },
  {
   "start": 28.0,
   "end": 28.82,
   "text": "It's red as an omen."
  },
  {
   "start": 29.46,
   "end": 31.08,
   "text": "Almost like inviting death to the table."
  },
  {
   "start": 31.92,
   "end": 36.08,
   "text": "Instead, you lay your chopsticks flat, across the top of the bowl, or on a little rest."
  },
  {
   "start": 36.82,
   "end": 41.78,
   "text": "Tiny gesture, completely different meaning, and these decked death related taboos get taken"
  },
  {
   "start": 41.78,
   "end": 46.64,
   "text": "even more seriously during the 7th lunar month, ghost month, when spirits are said to roam"
  },
  {
   "start": 46.64,
   "end": 49.46,
   "text": "and people avoid anything that might invite bad luck."
  },
  {
   "start": 49.88,
   "end": 53.74,
   "text": "It's just two sticks and a bowl of rice, but stand them up and you've turned dinner"
  },
  {
   "start": 53.74,
   "end": 57.64,
   "text": "into a funeral, which is exactly why, in China, you simply never do it."
  },
  {
   "start": 57.64,
   "end": 62.04,
   "text": "Half of good manners, it turns out, is just very old beliefs frozen into etiquette."
  },
  {
   "start": 62.52,
   "end": 63.84,
   "text": "Want to actually start learning Chinese?"
  },
  {
   "start": 64.48,
   "end": 68.66,
   "text": "Discover thousands of free exercises and more learning content on stacktags.io"
  }
 ]
}